<SubPage
  title="elliodelics · accessibility"
  description="The accessibility statement for elliodelics. Built to WCAG 2.2 level AAA, with the evidence and the one documented exception."
  heading="Accessibility"
>
  <p class="intro">
    This site is built to meet the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines
    (WCAG) 2.2 at level AAA, the strictest tier. For a field where
    confidentiality and access are ethics rather than checkboxes, the
    studio site should hold itself to the same standard.
  </p>

  <h2>What that means here</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Every text color measures at least 7 to 1 contrast against its background.</li>
    <li>Every control works with a keyboard and shows a visible focus ring.</li>
    <li>Click and tap targets are at least 44 pixels on every kind of device, except links inside sentences, which the standard exempts.</li>
    <li>All motion honors your reduced motion setting. The page works fully with animation off.</li>
    <li>Content never hides behind animation. Every word is on the page from the first frame, and scroll motion draws only the decorations.</li>
    <li>The site respects Windows High Contrast and other forced color modes.</li>
    <li>A <a href="/plain">plain words version</a> of the site is available for easier reading.</li>
    <li>A <a href="/vocabulary">vocabulary appendix</a> defines the field terms and abbreviations used on the site.</li>
    <li>No cookies, no trackers, no forms. Nothing to consent to, nothing to get stuck in.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>One known exception</h2>
  <p>
    The artwork behind the hero heading can be painted with a mouse or a
    finger. It is decoration. It holds no information and does nothing.
    Keyboard users see the same artwork paint itself when the page loads.
  </p>

  <h2>How we check</h2>
  <p>
    Contrast is measured computationally against the WCAG formula. Every
    page is scanned with axe-core, walked end to end with a keyboard, and
    reviewed through the accessibility tree a screen reader receives, with
    forced colors and reduced motion emulated in a real browser. This
    happens whenever the design changes, not once a year. If something
    here doesn't work for you, that's a bug. Email
    <a href="mailto:mike@elliodelics.com">mike@elliodelics.com</a> and it
    gets fixed.
  </p>

  <p class="mono reviewed">last reviewed · july 2026</p>
</SubPage>
